    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.1.1a-3a"/>
                <note type="curatorial">1a</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <fw type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</fw>
                    
                    <dateline>10-25-98</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Priests of Pallas Den.</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>7th Lydia K. C.</addrLine>
                    </address> 
                    
                    <salute>Dear Son J. G.</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>I am having a good time nothing to do, plenty to eat and I have a really good
                    <unclear/> of my own <unclear/> which to sleep and plenty of good caves too. I
                    have gained six friends since coming north. We will in all probability be
                    <unclear/> out of service between now and the 15th of Nov. I have just finished
                    a letter <del/> one to each Miss Lu Lu and one to Miss Grace. <unclear/></p>
                <p>I have <unclear/> to go to <unclear/> and there I am the <unclear/> or Country,
                    or a Reg of infantry that are billed for <unclear/>.</p> 
                <p>I will have to bear my own experience</p>
                <p>I could join anyone of the three Reg. Mo. Vol. but <unclear/> I wish to get that 7000 mile ride to the Phillipines if I am and as the saying goes a man the boys if I never get back I guess that you were at Omaha and that your <unclear/> a glorious time tell it? will you join me?</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.1.1a-3a"/>
                <note type="authorial">2 one</note>
                <note type="curatorial">2a</note>
                
                <p>and blankets</p>
                <p>I did not get ot see all the folks up their you asked me a question about Pearl Reborn that I am sorry to say that am unable to give a satisfactory answer and too, their is <unclear/> between a pretty woman and a handsome one did you ever consider that? and truly one whom I mgith admire you might not; though truly being my son-and of my blood.</p> 
                <p>Miss Pearl was sick when I was at and called on Mrs. Hodges! Excuse good Evening 2 once sheet 1st loge
                a  I hows and sold <unclear/> two <unclear/> <unclear/> more in one room is quite a right a number of merchants contracted with the War department to feed us they are doing very well and we get more and better <unclear/> <unclear/> than we <unclear/> JOhnnie I wish you were here a few days for to see me and the soldiers K. I has been very good to the boy indeed. did you see the President? I was over to Mr. Hodges a few weeks ago and in there my knapsack and it well filled with clothing</p> 

                <pb facs="nei.j4b.1.1a-3a"/>
                <note type="curatorial">3a</note>
                
<p>address</p>
                <closer>
<address>
    <addrLine>N. N. Neihardt</addrLine>
    <addrLine>Co. D 5th mo Vol</addrLine>
    <addrLine>Kan.</addrLine> 
    <addrLine>billy</addrLine> 
</address>
                </closer>
            </div1>
            
